window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>I’m a pixie.</p> <p>If there was a level zero of supernaturals, I’d be on the sub-basement level.</p> <p>I’m not super-strong or fast or crazy-smart, and the little bit of pixie magic I do have is limited to the most basic things that any human street magician can do.</p> <p>So when a pack of coyote shifters and their Alpha start hunting me and threatening the only remaining family I have left, I realize I’m going to need some paranormal help to fight them off. I do the only sane thing I can think to do. I flee to Moonhaven Cove and beg help from the local PNW council and the town’s sheriff.</p> <p>It seemed like such a well-thought-out plan...until the council lets Hux and his creepy pack of coyotes in.</p> <p>So now, in between dodging homicidal coyote shifters, I’m working with the sexy star elf at his comedy club, helping the unluckiest leprechaun ever avoid carnivorous office equipment, hanging out with a genie, and becoming BFFs with the lion shifter sheriff who is strangely attached to his strawberry yogurt. I don’t really have time for a relationship.</p> <p>But when Rhys looks at me, I forget the many reasons starting something with him would be a terrible idea. Rhys is tender, kind, flirty, and fun. He makes me laugh. And before long…I can’t imagine living the rest of my life without him.</p> <p>Trouble, thy name is Paradise Hart.</p> <p><i>Pixie Problems</i> is part of my new Moonhaven Cove series. Each book in the series can be listened to as a standalone, but listeners will get a fuller experience hearing them in order. If you’re looking for clean paranormal romance with swoony kisses, snappy dialogue, funny and heartwarming characters, and plenty of suspense and action, you’ve found the right place. Welcome to Moonhaven Cove.</p>"; 
